es.com/?scp=1-spot&sq=on%20par&st=cse \"On Par\"] columnist and sports reporter\n* [[James Risen]], national security correspondent\n* [[David E. Sanger]], Washington correspondent\n* [[Charlie Savage]], legal affairs correspondent\n* [[A. O. Scott]], film critic\n* [[Robert B. Semple, Jr.]], associate editor, Times editorial page, [[Pulitzer Prize]] winner\n* [[Scott Shane]], national security correspondent\n* [[Andrew Ross Sorkin]], chief mergers & acquisitions correspondent\n* [[Neil Strauss]], freelance music writer\n* [[Anthony Tommasini]], chief music critic\n* [[David C. Unger]], foreign affairs editorial writer\n* [[Pete Wells]], restaurant critic\n* [[Sheryl WuDunn]], industry and international business editor and Pulitzer Prize winner\n* Douglas Martin (reporter), obituaries\n* [[Rory Smith (journalist)|Rory Smith]], chief soccer correspondent\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Former==\n\n===Publishers===\n*[[George Jones (publisher)|George Jones]] (1851-1891)\n*[[George F. Spinney]] (1893-1896)\n*[[Adolph Ochs]] (1896-1935)\n*[[Arthur Hays Sulzberger]] (1935-1961)\n*[[Orvil Dryfoos]] (1961-1963)\n*[[Arthur Ochs Sulzberger|Arthur Ochs \"Punch\" Sulzberger]] (1963-1992)\n*[[Arthur Ochs Sulzberger Jr.]] (1992-2017)\n\n===Editor in Chief===\n*[[Henry Jarvis Raymond]] (1851-1869)\n*[[Charles Ransom Miller]] (1883-1922)\n\n===Executive editors===\n(position created in 1964 superseding Managing Editor as top news official)\n*[[Turner Catledge]] (1964\u20131968)\n*[[James Reston]] (1968\u20131969)\n*position vacant (1969\u20131976)\n*[[A. M. Rosenthal]] (1977\u20131986)\n*[[Max Frankel]] (1986\u20131994)\n*[[Joseph Lelyveld]] (1994\u20132001) and briefly in 2003\n*[[Howell Raines]] (2001\u20132003)\n* [[Bill Keller]] (2003\u20132011)\n* [[Jill Abramson]] (2011\u20132014)\n* [[Dean Baquet]] (2014\u2013)\n\n===Managing editors===\n*[[George F. Spinney]] (1889-1893)\n\n<!--*(under Ochs ownership with full authority over news separate from opinion editors:)-->\n*[[Carr Van Anda]] (1904-1932)\n*[[Edwin Leland James]] (1932-1951)\n*[[Turner Catledge]] (1952-1964)\n*[[Clifton Daniel]] (1964-1968)\n*[[A. M. Rosenthal]] (1968-1977)\n*[[Seymour Topping]] (1977-1986)\n*[[Arthur Gelb]] (1986-1989)\n*[[Joseph Lelyveld]] (1990-1994)\n*[[Gene Roberts (journalist)|Gene Roberts]] (1994-1997)\n\n===Editorial page editors===\n''Titled Editor-in-Chief or Editor until retirement of Merz but never had authority over news pages.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/17/insider/2007-2016-the-rosenthal-era-in-the-editorial-department.html|title=2007-2016 - The Rosenthal Era in the Editorial Department|first=David W.|last=Dunlap|date=18 March 2016|publisher=|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n*[[Rollo Ogden]] (1922-1937)\n*[[John Huston Finley]] (1937-1938)\n*[[Charles Merz (editor)|Charles Merz]] (1938-1961)<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/1977/09/01/archive/charles-merz-a-former-times-editor-is-dead-at-84.html</ref>\n*[[John Bertram Oakes]] (1961-1976)\n*[[Max Frankel]] (1977-1986)\n*[[Jack Rosenthal]] (1986-1993)\n*[[Howell Raines]] (1993-2001)\n*[[Gail Collins]] (2001-2006)\n*[[Andrew Rosenthal]] (2007-2016)\n\n===Other former personnel===\n\u2022 William E. Sauro, staff photographer. Won George Polk Award 1965.\n* [[Brooks Atkinson]], theater critic\n* [[Matt Bai]], news analyst and [http://topics.nytimes.com/top/news/washington/columns/political-times/index.html \"Political Times\"] columnist\n* [[Clive Barnes]], dance and theater critic\n* [[Jayson Blair]], reporter (1999\u20132003); resigned over plagiarism and fabrications<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2003/05/11/national/11PAPE.html?ex=1217563200&en=b83fbfe282d28587&ei=5070 \"Times Reporter Who Resigned Leaves Long Trail of Deception\"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', May 11, 2003. Accessed July 30, 2008.</ref>\n* [[Raymond Bonner]], civil war reporter in [[El Salvador]]; resigned in protest\n* [[Don Hogan Charles]], photographer<ref>*{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/projects/cp/national/unpublished-black-history/don-hogan-charlesa-day-in-the-life-of-harlem-1966 |title=The Harlem of Don Hogan Charles |first=James |last=Estrin |authorlink=James Estrin |date=February 15, 2016 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=December 25, 2017 }}</ref>\n* [[Adam Clymer]], former correspondent in [[Washington, D.C.]]\n* [[William G. Connolly]], co-author of ''[[The New York Times Manual of Style and Usage]]''\n* [[Bill Cunningham (American photographer)|Bill Cunningham]], fashion photographer\n* [[Kurt Eichenwald]], business reporter\n* [[Janet Elder]], deputy managing editor (died 2017)\n* Leonard P. Forman, chief financial officer (2001-2007)\n* James M. Follo, chief financial officer (2007-2018)\n* [[Vanessa Friedman]], fashion critic\n* [[Linda Greenhouse]], U.S. Supreme Court correspondent, Pulitzer Prize winner\n* [[Trish Hall]], [[Masthead (American publishing)|masthead]] editor overseeing six feature sections (2010\u20132011), [[op-ed]] editor (2011\u20132015), and senior editor (2015\u20132017)\n* [[Cathy Horyn]], fashion critic (1998\u20132014) \n* [[Bernard Holland]], music critic (1981\u20131994), chief music critic (1995\u20132008)\n* [[Walter Kerr]], theater critic\n* [[Anna Kisselgoff]], dance critic from 1968, chief dance critic (1977-2005)\n* [[Arthur Krock]], Pulitzer Prize winning correspondent and columnist\n* [[Trymaine Lee]], Harlem beat reporter (2006\u20132011)\n* [[Christopher Lehmann-Haupt]], book reviewer\n* [[Eric Lichtblau]], legal affairs reporter\n* [[Hugo Lindgren]], editor, ''The New York Times Magazine'' (2010\u20132013)\n* [[Judith Miller]], reporter, jailed for refusing to reveal sources\n* [[Rajiv Pant]], chief technology officer (2011-2015)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/cmo/2015/05/07/new-york-times-cto-rajiv-pant-joins-digital-media-startup-some-spider/|title=New York Times CTO Rajiv Pant Joins Digital Media Startup Some Spider|last=Alpert|first=Lukas I.|date=2015-05-07|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-08}}</ref>\n* [[Dith Pran]], photojournalist during Cambodian war\n* [[Harrison Salisbury]], Pulitzer Prize and George Polk Award winner \n* [[Sydney Schanberg]], Pulitzer Prize and George Polk Award winner; resigned in protest.\n* [[Allan M. Siegal]], co-author of ''[[The New York Times Manual of Style and Usage]]''\n* [[Louis Silverstein]], design director\n* [[Hedrick Smith]], correspondent and bureau chief\n* [[Barbara Strauch]], editor (2000\u20132015)\n* [[Walter Sullivan (journalist)|Walter Sullivan]], science editor\n* [[John Swinton (journalist)|John Swinton]], chief editorialist (1860\u20131869)\n* [[Howard Thompson - (film critic)|Howard Thompson]], film critic\n* [[Don Van Natta, Jr.]], Pulitzer Prize winning investigative correspondent\n* [[Sean Villafranca]], design manager (1998\u20132008)\n* [[Sarah Jeong]], Editorial Board<ref>{{cite news |title=Sarah Jeong Joins The Times\u2019s Editorial Board\n |url=https://www.nytco.com/sarah-jeong-joins-the-timess-editorial-board |accessdate=2 August 2018|date=2 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Public editors===\nThe public editor position was established in 2003 in response to the [[Jayson Blair]] scandal. In late May 2017, ''The New York Times'' announced that it was eliminating the post. Arthur Ochs Sulzberger Jr. announced: \"The public editor position, created in the aftermath of a grave journalistic scandal, played a crucial part in rebuilding our readers\u2019 trusts by acting as our in-house watchdog. We welcomed that criticism, even when it stung. But today, our followers on social media and our readers across the internet have come together to collectively serve as a modern watchdog, more vigilant and forceful than one person could ever be.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/2017/05/31/new-york-times-buyouts/102344652/|title=The New York Times offers newsroom buyouts, eliminates public editor post|work=USA TODAY|access-date=2017-06-04|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Daniel Okrent]] (2003\u20132005) \n* [[Byron Calame]] (2005\u20132007)\n* [[Clark Hoyt]] (2007\u20132010)\n* [[Arthur S. Brisbane]] (2010\u20132012)\n* [[Margaret Sullivan (journalist)|Margaret Sullivan]] (2012\u20132016)\n* [[Elizabeth Spayd]] (2016\u20132017)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{NY Times}}\n\n[[Category:The New York Times people|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of people by company|The New York Times]]\n[[Category:Employees by company]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Cleanup|reason=this list is both incomplete and out-of-date; indeed, the information it purports to enumerate is hard to come by reliably and without original research. And Yet: |date=January 2017}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''The New York Times'' employees}}\nThis is a list of former and current ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' employees, reporters, and columnists.\n\n==Current==\n\n===Publisher===\n* [[Arthur Gregg Sulzberger]] (2018\u2013present)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/20/business/media/new-york-times-names-ag-sulzberger-deputy-publisher.html|title=New York Times Names A.G. Sulzberger Deputy Publisher|last=Ember|first=Sydney|date=2016-10-19|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-08-26|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/14/business/media/a-g-sulzberger-new-york-times-publisher.html</ref>\n\n===Masthead<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/admin/the-new-york-times-masthead.html|title=The Masthead of The New York Times.|date=2017-04-04|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-02-20|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>===\n{|\n|valign=\"top\"|\n'''News'''\n* [[Dean Baquet]], executive editor\n* [[Joseph Kahn (journalist)|Joseph Kahn]], managing editor\n* [[Rebecca Blumenstein]], deputy managing editor\n* [[Tom Bodkin]], creative director\n* [[Matthew Purdy]], deputy managing editor\n* [[Rebecca Corbett]], assistant editor\n* [[Sam Dolnick]], assistant managing editor\n* Monica